    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-pork-and-beef-bolognese-conchiglie/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>mince </strong>to the dish with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until nicely browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-pork-and-beef-bolognese-conchiglie/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the mince is browning, top, tail and coarsely grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> (no need to peel!)</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-pork-and-beef-bolognese-conchiglie/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated carrot</strong>,<strong> diced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the dish with your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and<strong> soy sauce</strong></p><p>Add 500ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [650ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[850ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> with your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil then put in the oven, uncovered, for an initial 10-15 min or until slightly thickened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-pork-and-beef-bolognese-conchiglie/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After an initial 10-15 min, add your <strong>conchiglie</strong> to the dish and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Return the dish to the oven, covered, for 25 min (stirring halfway) or until the pasta is tender and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>all in one pork & beef bolognese conchiglie</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-pork-and-beef-bolognese-conchiglie/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-pork-and-beef-bolognese-conchiglie/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Leave the <strong>all in one pork & beef bolognese conchiglie</strong> to stand for 5 min before serving (this helps the flavours to develop)</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-pork-and-beef-bolognese-conchiglie/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>all in one</strong> <strong>pork & beef bolognese conchiglie</strong> topped with your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
